<paragraph id="8BD31167FFC3FFF7F8705FC95C00F606" blockId="46.[1996,2591,1984,2407]" lastBlockId="46.[1387,2595,2421,3274]" pageId="46" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis id="B918CD75FFC3FFF7F8705FC95209F849" bold="true" box="[1996,2152,1984,2013]" pageId="46" pageNumber="598">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C6AE4FFC3FFF7F7375FC95270F790" authority="Thomas, 1916" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Nelomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="598" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lamarum">Nelomys lamarum Thomas, 1916</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B041B3AFFC3FFF7F7905FEE53C9F75D" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804303329" pageId="46" pageNumber="598">“Lamarao, Bahia, about 70 miles N.W. of Bahia city [= Salvador]. Alt. 300 mm [sic].” Amended by L. H. Emmons and colleagues in 2002 to “LLamarao, about 70 miles NW of Salvador, Bahia, Brazil, 11°47’S 38°53’W,elev. 300 m.”</materialsCitation>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C6AE4FFC3FFF7F87350C6522AF764" authorityName="Lund" authorityYear="1839" box="[1999,2123,2255,2288]" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Phyllomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="598" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Phyllomys</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C6AE4FFC3FFF7F7E650C652AFF764" box="[2138,2254,2255,2288]" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Nelomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="598" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lamarum">lamarum</taxonomicName>
was formerly classified in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C6AE4FFC3FFF7F71650F25370F68C" authorityName="G. Cuvier" authorityYear="1809" box="[2218,2321,2299,2328]" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Echimys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="598" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Echimys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C6AE4FFC3FFF7F6DB50F253AFF68C" authorityName="Jourdan" authorityYear="1837" box="[2407,2510,2299,2328]" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Nelomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="598" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nelomys</taxonomicName>
. It is closely related to P. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C6AE4FFC3FFF7F75751175314F6AB" authorityName="Lund" authorityYear="1840" box="[2283,2421,2334,2367]" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Phyllomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="598" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
, divergence of these two species is a relatively recent event. Monotypic
</paragraph>
